From a5091a5dd74365fa1bf55c32109ede614811372c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: quivent <quivent@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Apr 2026 14:07:45 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] feat(qwen3next): MTP (NextN) head graph builder + load path

- Register NEXTN tensor enums for LLM_ARCH_QWEN3NEXT so loader knows
  blk.*.nextn.{eh_proj,enorm,hnorm,embed_tokens,shared_head_*}.
- Read LLM_KV_NEXTN_PREDICT_LAYERS for QWEN3NEXT hparams (optional).
- Load the 6 NextN tensors into layer.nextn.* for the last
  nextn_predict_layers layers of a qwen3next model. All marked
  TENSOR_NOT_REQUIRED so existing models without MTP still load.
- Add llama_model::has_mtp_head() helper: true iff every expected
  NextN layer has a populated eh_proj.
- Add llm_build_qwen3next::build_mtp_head(prev_hidden, tok_embed, il,
  out_hidden) implementing one MTP layer forward pass:
    h_n = hnorm(prev_hidden); e_n = enorm(tok_embed)
    h = eh_proj(concat([e_n, h_n]))         # CRITICAL: embed first
    h += o_proj(sigmoid(gate) * SDPA(Q,K,V)) # gated attention, pos 0
    h += mlp_down(SiLU(mlp_gate) * mlp_up)   # dense MLP
    logits = shared_head_head(shared_head_norm(h))
  Uses manual single-token attention (no KV cache, no mask) to match
  the MLX reference in ~/mlx-fork/fused_gdn.py MTPHead.__call__,
  including the embed-first concat order (was the primary correctness
  pitfall called out in the task brief).
- Expose public C API:
    bool   llama_model_has_mtp_head(const llama_model *)
    int32_t llama_mtp_draft(ctx, last_token, n_draft, out_tokens, out_logits)
  has_mtp_head is fully functional. mtp_draft is wired and validates
  inputs; it returns -4 until the MTP-only graph execution path is
  added via a new llm_graph_type (follow-up work; the builder is
  ready to be called from process_ubatch).

Known follow-ups:
  1. New LLM_GRAPH_TYPE_MTP + process_ubatch route to run the graph.
  2. Capture + surface of the previous decoder hidden state
     (pre-output-norm) from the main decode pass.
  3. RMSNorm +1.0 convention check: shared_head_norm weight may be
     stored w or (1+w) depending on how GGUF conversion baked it.
     Build passes; verify against reference logits once execution
     is wired.

